Review: This could have been fun and silly but that third act was TURBO CRINGE🫣🫣
I am not drinking any FUCKING MERLOT!
I’m bumping this up half a star only because Charles Melton just pulled off a Brando right before my eyes and I still can’t believe it.

Me personally, I wouldn’t have just sat there while my wife flirted in Korean with her childhood sweetheart. I’d be all like “hey - whatcha guys talking about? …they have those, like, cool tech-y markets in Korea right?… What?”
Third Act absolutely made this movie for me
Epic highs in between pretty great stuff
Extra points for talky talky 50s flair

Movie: Home Alone 2: Lost in New York
Review: I love how this time Kevin’s just straight up trying to murder them
This movie just slowly crawled inside of me and set up camp in my brain. Can’t stop thinking about it - sensational and important.
Went into this totally ready to hate it aaaandddd…like thirty minutes in I gave up. This was just a chocolatey delight. Although I will say Chalamet did have some turbo cringe moments as expected.
